Package rs.edu.raf.test.model.questions

Contains various types of questions, all extending the Question class.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    QuestionInterface  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Question
    Abstract class that represent Question
    QuestionBasic
    Basic questions are composed of one question with multiple possible answers, including the correct answer and several incorrect answers.
    QuestionFillTheBlank
    Fill-the-bank questions are composed of one question with one or multiple wholes in text left for students to put in right word or sentence.
    QuestionMatching
    Students respond to matching questions by pairing each of a set of stems with one of the choices provided on the exam.
    QuestionSurvey
    Survey question represent question where student or examinee give their opinion about the question For example how much are they satisfied with some product, etc.
    QuestionTrueOrFalse
    True/false questions are only composed of a statement.
    StatementInQuestionSurvey  

Package rs.edu.raf.test.model.questions Description
